    "file": "internal/terraform/context_apply.go",
    "line": 191,
    "severity": "high",
    "description": "DeferralAllowed is hardcoded to true during the apply walk, but it should be false for the standard modules runtime. During the plan walk (context_plan.go:723), DeferralAllowed comes from opts.DeferralAllowed which defaults to false for standard Terraform (only the stacks runtime sets it to true). Hardcoding true during apply allows resources to be silently deferred during the apply phase even when they were fully planned. This can cause: (1) resources that should be applied to instead be silently deferred (incomplete apply without errors), (2) node_module_expand.go allowing unknown for_each/count values during apply when they should be known, and (3) inconsistent behavior between the plan and apply phases. The stacks runtime has its own apply path and does not use context_apply.go, so DeferralAllowed should be false here.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/internal/terraform/context_apply.go
+++ b/internal/terraform/context_apply.go
@@ -188,7 +188,7 @@ func (c *Context) ApplyAndEval(plan *plans.Plan, config *configs.Config, opts *A
 		Overrides:               plan.Overrides,
 		ExternalProviderConfigs: opts.ExternalProviders,

